{"title":"Bedrock Sandals Team Up with Ron’s Bikes for Ultra Tulip Adventure Sandals","link":"https://bikerumor.com/bedrock-sandals-rons-bikes-collaboration-ultra-tulip-adventure-sandals/","date":1692198000000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-phone.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals on the phone\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-phone.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-phone-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-phone-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-phone-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-phone-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-phone-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Another cool collaboration just landed on a trail near you. Hailing from Missoula, Montana,<a href=\"https://bedrocksandals.com/\" target=\"_blank\"> adventure sandal makers</a>, Bedrock Sandals has just completed their first-ever collaboration. And who better to collaborate with than <a href=\"https://ronsbikes.com/products/bedrock-x-rons-ultra-tulip-special-x11-small-chest?syclid=cjds1jqusvis07rv9npg&amp;utm_campaign=emailmarketing_169438544147&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=shopify_email\" target=\"_blank\">Neoclassical bike stuff</a> maker, Ron’s Bikes? More specifically, Bedrock wearer extraordinaire, Ultra Romance himself.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-in-the-wild.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-in-the-wild-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals in the wild\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-in-the-wild-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-in-the-wild-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-in-the-wild-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-in-the-wild-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-in-the-wild-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-in-the-wild.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Bedrock has incorporated the signature Ron’s Bikes tulip design on the straps of their Cairn Pro II, and Cairn 3D Geo sandals, deeming them the Limited Edition Ultra Tulip Sandals. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-getting-wet.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-getting-wet-800x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals getting wet\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-getting-wet-800x1200.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-getting-wet-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-getting-wet-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-getting-wet-768x1152.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-getting-wet.jpeg 853w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. Bedrock Sandals, Ron’s Bikes</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-over-a-log.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-over-a-log-800x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals over a log\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-over-a-log-800x1200.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-over-a-log-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-over-a-log-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-over-a-log-768x1152.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-over-a-log.jpeg 853w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Ron says that the pattern “<em>looks like camo from afar, and flower power up close.  A muscular hippie — the archetype of both our brands</em>“.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I’ve personally been an enthusiastic user of Bedrock Sandals since 2017, and currently in the middle of a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bedrock-mountain-clogs-for-cycling/\" target=\"_blank\">long-term review</a> of their synthetic leather version of their Mountain Clog. I’ve been riding in my Cairns almost exclusively for the last 5 or 6 years, and it’s been an overall pleasant experience. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Bedrock Ultra-Tulip Sandals</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-bike.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-bike-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals on the bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-bike-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-bike-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-bike-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-bike-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-bike-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-on-the-bike.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned earlier, this collab will be coming in two distinct soles, the Cairn Pro II, and Cairn 3D Geo soles. They are both retailing for $130 but there are only 300 pairs available in this collaboration. So, if you like ’em, go get ’em. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Cairn Pro II Adventure Sandals</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-up-close.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-up-close-800x800.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals up close\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-up-close-800x800.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-up-close-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-up-close-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-up-close-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-up-close.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-side-shot.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-side-shot-800x800.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals side shot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-side-shot-800x800.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-side-shot-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-side-shot-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-side-shot-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-side-shot.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cairn Pro ll is a beefier version of the original Cairn and is what they call “our best in performance”. This is their “ultimate adventure sandal, outfitted with their Hook-heel strap and Vibram Megagrip outsole with the molded 3D footbed on top. The Pro II G-hook and loop system locks in the heel strap like it does the front, for a super secure fit.  </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Cairn 3D Geo</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-800x800.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals Geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-800x800.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-side.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-side-800x800.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Ultra Tulip Sandals Geo side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-side-800x800.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-side-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-side-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-side-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Ultra-Tulip-Sandals-Geo-side.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cairn Geo is Bedrock’s “flagship eco-groovy sandal”. It’s built with the same tried-and-true Cairn strap design yet geared towards more casual uses. it uses an exclusive brown Vibram outsole that dawns wider spread, less aggressive lugs and is crafted with Vibram Eco-Step compound comprised of 30% recycled material. It’s really geared for dry conditions and is suggested to go for the Cairn Adventure Pro for wet activities. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ron’s Matching Ultra Tulip Luggage</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Fab's Chest\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Ron’s Bikes matched the webbing and incorporated it into a limited run of 50 small Fab’s Chests. These bags use Connecticut made cotton faced x-pac laminate, and come in brown and tan. The body and pockets of the bag used the 1” tulip webbing to contrast the main extendable flap. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-and-sandals.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"540\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-and-sandals.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Fab's Chest and sandals\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-and-sandals.jpeg 540w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-and-sandals-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-and-sandals-80x120.jpeg 80w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-with-Ron.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"540\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-with-Ron.jpeg\" alt=\"Bedrock X Ron's Bikes Fab's Chest with Ron\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-with-Ron.jpeg 540w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-with-Ron-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bedrock-X-Rons-Bikes-Fabs-Chest-with-Ron-80x120.jpeg 80w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, the inside of the bag is lined with a special brown and tan tulip pattern. Ron says he “hopes you like brown”. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Ultra Tulip Bedrock sandals and matching bag will be sold separately from each company’s separate websites. With the <a href=\"https://bedrocksandals.com/collections/bedrock-x-rons-bikes-ultra-tulip-sandals\" target=\"_blank\">Sandals</a> being made in Montana, and the <a href=\"https://ronsbikes.com/products/bedrock-x-rons-ultra-tulip-special-x11-small-chest?syclid=cjds1jqusvis07rv9npg&amp;utm_campaign=emailmarketing_169438544147&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=shopify_email\" target=\"_blank\">Fab’s Chests</a> being made in Connecticut, this seems to make sense. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>See below to get yours while supplies last. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://bedrocksandals.com/\" target=\"_blank\">BedRockSandals.com</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://ronsbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">RonsBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bedrock-sandals-rons-bikes-collaboration-ultra-tulip-adventure-sandals/\">Bedrock Sandals Team Up with Ron’s Bikes for Ultra Tulip Adventure Sandals</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3e4cfe3ef84f1a800350ad2970fcd0ef213bd747a9f8cd0b48a455a447f1152a","category":"Cycling"}